	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Alright, did it <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />  
<br />
<br />What it seems to me is that the nametable itself deals with the background...  and I'm guessing that vertical mirroring is called so because the background tiles(?) generate vertically from top to bottom.  I haven't tested any horizontal yet, but I'm guessing the tiles lay out horizontally.  I think the scroll line shows where the left side of the screen is.
<br />
<br />Now, I noticed that the nametable at $2000 and $2800 (like in Membler's post on the other thread), as well as $2400 and $2C00(?) are the exact same.  Why is this?  I don't understand exactly what it accomplishes when it looks to me like the addresses at $2000 and $2400 are doing enough... or is there something that $2800 and $2C00 are doing that I'm not aware of that add to it?  
<br />
<br />By the way, I tested mainly with Mega Man 2 and Super Mario Bros. 2 (USA).

		

		</td>
